The Swiss Ascom Holding AG  company Tuesday announced the sale of its cable network in Switzerland and  Austria.
Addressing an international management symposium here, Fred Sutter,  chairman of the group, indicated the sale would be worth about 200 million  Swiss francs (142 million dollars).
Ascom, which suffered losses last year of 337 million Swiss francs (240  million dollars), announced in March it intended selling its cable network to  a company formed by the Swiss postal and telephone service, Fischer Holding AG  and Siemens Albis AG.
